===Noun===
'''byte''' ([[bytes]])

{{wikipedia}}
# A [[sequence]] of [[adjacent]] bits, almost always eight, [[operated]] on as a [[unit]] by a [[computer]]; can [[represent]] an [[integer]] from 0 to 255, a [[pair]] of [[hexadecimal]] [[digit]]s each from 0 to F, a pair of [[packed decimal]] digits each from 0 to 9, a packed decimal digit and a sign or a single [[character]]
#: ''The word “hello” fits into 5 '''bytes''' of ASCII code.''

